                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/3–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crocker</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-24T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 24, 1945—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>471. The draft ATC agreement modified as indicated in your 510, March 6,<note
                        n="26" xml:id="d321fn26">Not printed.</note> and with the substituted
                    article 2 quoted in urtel 630, March 22, is acceptable to the Department, ATC,
                    and War Department. You are hereby authorized to conclude negotiations by an
                    exchange of notes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
